V{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] -->\u000a| name = Kit Fine\u000a| image       =\u000a| caption=\u000a| imagesize   = \u000a| birth_name = \u000a| education = Ph.D. 1969 (philosophy), [[University of Warwick]]; B.A. 1967 ([[Philosophy, Politics and Economics|philosophy]]), [[University of Oxford]]\u000a| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1946|03|26|df=yes}}\u000a| birth_place = \u000a| influences  = [[Arthur Prior]]\u000a| influenced  =\u000a| nationality = British\u000a| occupation = Professor of Philosophy and Mathematics\u000a| spouse = [[Anne Fine]] (divorced)\u000a| children = [[Cordelia Fine]], Ione Fine\u000a| website = {{URL|http://philosophy.fas.nyu.edu/object/kitfine}}\u000a}}\u000a\u000a'''Kit Fine''' (born 26 March 1946) is a Silver Professor of [[Philosophy]] and [[Mathematics]] at [[New York University]]  in the [[NYU Department of Philosophy]]. He previously taught for several years at the [[University of Michigan]] and at [[UCLA]]. The author of several books and dozens of articles in international academic journals, he has made notable contributions to the fields of [[philosophical logic]], [[metaphysics]], and the [[philosophy of language]] and also has written on [[ancient philosophy]], in particular on [[Aristotle]]'s account of logic and modality.\u000a\u000aHe is also a Distinguished Research Professor in the Department of Philosophy, University of Birmingham, UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.birmingham.ac.uk/staff/profiles/philosophy/fine-kit.aspx |title=Professor Kit Fine - Department of Philosophy - University of Birmingham |publisher=Birmingham.ac.uk |date= |accessdate=2015-10-19}}</ref>\u000a\u000a==Life and writings==\u000aAfter graduating from the University of Oxford (B.A., 1967) Fine received his Ph.D. from the [[University of Warwick]] in 1969, under the supervision of [[A. N. Prior]]. He was elected a Corresponding Fellow of the [[British Academy]] in 2005<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.britac.ac.uk/fellowship/elections/2005/index.cfm |title=British Academy &#124; Elections to the Fellowship 2005 - British Academy |publisher=Britac.ac.uk |date= |accessdate=2015-10-19}}</ref> and a Fellow of the [[American Academy of Arts & Sciences]] in 2006.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://leiterreports.typepad.com/blog/2006/04/new_philosophy__1.html |title=Leiter Reports: A Philosophy Blog: New Philosophy Fellows of the American Academy of Arts & Sciences (Leiter) |publisher=Leiterreports.typepad.com |date=2006-04-22 |accessdate=2015-10-19}}</ref> He has held fellowships from the [[John Simon Guggenheim Memorial Foundation]] and the [[American Council of Learned Societies]] and is a former editor of the [[Journal of Symbolic Logic]]. In addition to his primary areas of research, he has written papers in [[ancient philosophy]], [[linguistics]], [[computer science]], and [[economic theory]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://philosophy.fas.nyu.edu/object/kitfine |title=Kit Fine, Faculty of Philosophy &#124; NYU |publisher=Philosophy.fas.nyu.edu |date= |accessdate=2015-10-19}}</ref>\u000a\u000aFine has described his general approach to philosophy as follows:  "I\u2019m firmly of the opinion that real progress in philosophy can only come from taking common sense seriously. A departure from common sense is usually an indication that a mistake has been made."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.3ammagazine.com/3am/metaphysical-kit/ |title=Metaphysical Kit » 3:AM Magazine |publisher=3ammagazine.com |date=2012-03-23 |accessdate=2015-10-19}}</ref>\u000a\u000aFine has two daughters from his former marriage to [[Anne Fine]]. Anne Fine is an author of children's books; [[Cordelia Fine]] teaches at a university in Australia; Ione Fine is a professor at the [[University of Washington]].<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/books/authorinterviews/7992667/Anne-Fine-author.html | location=London | work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] | first=Jessica | last=Salter | title=World of Anne Fine, author | date=14 September 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://faculty.washington.edu/ionefine/ |title=FineLab homepage |publisher=Faculty.washington.edu |date= |accessdate=2015-07-15}}</ref>\u000a\u000a==Bibliography==\u000a* ''Semantic Relationism''. Blackwell, 2007. ISBN 978-1-4051-0844-7\u000a* ''Modality and Tense: Philosophical Papers''. Oxford University Press, 2005. ISBN 0-19-927871-7\u000a* ''The Limits of Abstraction''. Oxford University Press, 2002. ISBN 0-19-924618-1\u000a* ''Reasoning With Arbitrary Objects''. Blackwell, 1986. ISBN 0-631-13844-7\u000a* ''Worlds, Times, and Selves'' (with [[A. N. Prior]]). [[University of Massachusetts Press]], 1977. ISBN 0-87023-227-4\u000a\u000a==Notes==\u000a<references />\u000a\u000a==References==\u000a*[http://silverdialogues.fas.nyu.edu/page/Kit_Fine Silver Dialogues: Kit Fine]\u000a*[http://silverdialogues.fas.nyu.edu/docs/CP/299/fine_cv.pdf Kit Fine's CV (2004)]\u000a\u000a==External links==\u000a* [http://philosophy.fas.nyu.edu/object/kitfine Fine's web page] at [[New York University]].\u000a* [http://www.birmingham.ac.uk/staff/profiles/philosophy/fine-kit.aspx Fine's web page] at [[University of Birmingham]].\u000a* [https://www.ontology.co/biblio/finek-biblio.htm Annotated Bibliography of Kit Fine's Writings (1970-2016).]\u000a* [https://www.ontology.co/biblio/finek-studies.htm Kit Fine. Annotated Bibliography of the Studies on His Philosophy.]\u000a* [http://www.3ammagazine.com/3am/metaphysical-kit/ Interview with 3AM Magazine]\u000a\u000a{{Authority control}}\u000a{{DEFAULTSORT:Fine, Kit}}\u000a[[Category:Living people]]\u000a[[Category:1946 births]]\u000a[[Category:British philosophers]]\u000a[[Category:Philosophers of language]]\u000a[[Category:Metaphysicians]]\u000a[[Category:Analytic philosophers]]\u000a[[Category:American logicians]]\u000a[[Category:Fellows of the British Academy]]\u000a[[Category:Fellows of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences]]\u000a[[Category:Alumni of the University of Warwick]]\u000a[[Category:Guggenheim Fellows]]\u000a[[Category:University of Michigan faculty]]
